                <head>No. 134.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 14, 1882</date>. (Received August
                        28.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 423.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my number 417, of the 8th instant, I
                    have the honor to acquaint you that I have to-day received from Lord Granville a
                    letter, dated on the 11th instant, in which he informs me that a communication
                    had been sent by the Irish government, reporting that Patrick Slattery, one of
                    the American suspects detained under the protection of person and property
                    (Ireland) act 1881, was released on the 1st instant.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. R. LOWELL.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
